INSERT INTO `widok_evo_site_tmplvar_contentvalues` VALUES ('1751','81','377','<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote1anc\" name=\"sdfootnote1sym\">1</a>Jes&uacute;s Carrillo, &ldquo;Democratic Institutions versus Culture Wars,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum: Constellations of Knowledge, Politics and Mediation: A&nbsp;Generator of Social Change</em>, ed. John Byrne, Elinor Morgan, November Paynter, Aida Sanchez de Serdio, and Adela Zeleznik (Amsterdam: Valiz, 2018), 234&ndash;42.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote2anc\" name=\"sdfootnote2sym\">2</a>Nina Moentmann, &ldquo;The Rise and Fall of New Institutionalism: Perspectives on a&nbsp;Possible Future,&rdquo; in <em>Art and Contemporary Critical Practice: Reinventing Institutional Critique</em>, ed. Gerald Raunig and Gene Ray (London: MayFly Books, 2009), 155&ndash;61.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote3anc\" name=\"sdfootnote3sym\">3</a>Claire Bishop, Dan Perjovschi, <em>Radical Museology or, &ldquo;What&rsquo;s Contemporary,&rdquo; in Museums of Contemporary Art?</em> (London: Koenig Books, 2014).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote4anc\" name=\"sdfootnote4sym\">4</a>Jerzy Ludwiński, <em>Notes from the Future of Art: Selected Writings of Jerzy Ludwiński</em> (Eindhoven; Rotterdam: Van Abbemuseum; Veenman Publishers, 2007), 26.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote5anc\" name=\"sdfootnote5sym\">5</a>Magdalena Zi&oacute;łkowska, &ldquo;Jerzy Ludwiński&rsquo;s Testing of the Dysfunction of the Museum: On the Museum of Current Art in Wrocław (1966),&rdquo; in <em>From Museum Critique to the Critical Museum</em>, ed. Katarzyna Murawska-Muthesius and Piotr Piotrowski (Farnham Surrey, England ; Burlington, VT: Ashgate, 2015), 81&ndash;98.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote6anc\" name=\"sdfootnote6sym\">6</a>Pierre Bourdieu, <em>The Rules of Art: Genesis and Structure of the Literary Field</em> (Cambridge: Polity Press, 1996).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote7anc\" name=\"sdfootnote7sym\">7</a>Tony Bennett, &ldquo;The Exhibitionary Complex&rdquo;, <em>New Formations</em>, no. 4 (Spring 1988): 73-102.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote8anc\" name=\"sdfootnote8sym\">8</a>Alexander Alberro, &ldquo;Institutions, Critique, and Institutional Critique,&rdquo; in <em>Institutional Critique: An Anthology of Artists&rsquo; Writings</em>, ed. Alexander Alberro and Blake Stimson (Cambridge, Mass: MIT Press, 2009).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote9anc\" name=\"sdfootnote9sym\">9</a>Lucy Lippard, <em>Six years: the dematerialisation of the art object from 1966 to 1972</em> (London: Studio Vista, 1973).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote10anc\" name=\"sdfootnote10sym\">10</a>Peter B&uuml;rger, <em>Theory of the avant-garde</em> (Manchester: Manchester University Press, 1984).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote11anc\" name=\"sdfootnote11sym\">11</a>Andrea Fraser, &ldquo;From the Critique of Institutions to an Institution of Critique,&rdquo; in <em>Institutional Critique and After</em>, ed. John C. Welchman (Zurich: JRP|Ringier, 2006), 123&ndash;37.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote12anc\" name=\"sdfootnote12sym\">12</a>Stephen Wright, <em>Toward a&nbsp;Lexicon of Usership</em> (Eindhoven: Van Abbemuseum, 2013); Stephen Wright, &ldquo;Escapology,&rdquo; in <em>Truth Is Concrete: A&nbsp;Handbook for Artistic Strategies in Real Politics</em>, ed. Florian Malzacher (Berlin; New York; Graz: Sternberg Press; Steirischer Herbst, 2014), 311&ndash;12.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote13anc\" name=\"sdfootnote13sym\">13</a>George Y&uacute;dice, <em>The Expediency of Culture: Uses of Culture in the Global Era</em> (Durham; London: Duke University Press, 2003).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote14anc\" name=\"sdfootnote14sym\">14</a>Hans Belting, Andrea Buddensieg, and Peter Weibel, eds., <em>The Global Contemporary and the Rise of New Art Worlds</em> (Karlsruhe; Cambridge; London: ZKM/Center for Art and Media; The MIT Press, 2013).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote15anc\" name=\"sdfootnote15sym\">15</a>Luc Boltanski, &ldquo;From Object to &OElig;uvre. The Process of Attribution and Valorization of Objects,&rdquo; in <em>Joy Forever. Political Economy of Social Creativity</em>, ed. Michal Kozlowski, Krystian Szadkowski, Agnieszka Kurant, Jan Sowa, and Jakub Szreder (London: MayFly Books, 2014), 17&ndash;49.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote16anc\" name=\"sdfootnote16sym\">16</a>Walter Benjamin, &ldquo;The Work of Art in the Age of Mechanical Reproduction,&rdquo; 1936. <a href=\"http://www.marxists.org/reference/subject/philosophy/works/ge/benjamin.htm\">http://www.marxists.org/reference/subject/philosophy/works/ge/ /benjamin.htm</a>, accessed August 22, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote17anc\" name=\"sdfootnote17sym\">17</a>Hito Steyerl, &ldquo;If You Don&rsquo;t Have Bread, Eat Art!: Contemporary Art and Derivative Fascisms,&rdquo; <em>e-flux journal</em>, October 2016, <a href=\"http://www.e-flux.com/journal/76/69732/if-you-don-t-have-bread-eat-art-contemporary-art-and-derivative-fascisms/\">http://www.e-flux.com/journal/76/69732/if-you-don-t-have-bread-eat-art-contemporary-art-and-derivative-fascisms/</a>, accessed: August 22, 2018; <em>European Cultural Policies 2015: A&nbsp;Report with Scenarios on the Future of Public Funding for Contemporary Art in Europe</em>, eds. Maria Lind, Raimund Minichbauer (Stockholm; Vienna: Iaspis; eipcp, 2005); Julian Stallabrass, <em>Art Incorporated: The Story of Contemporary Art</em> (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2004).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote18anc\" name=\"sdfootnote18sym\">18</a>Andrea Fraser, &ldquo;From the Critique of Institutions to an Institution of Critique,&rdquo; in <em>Institutional Critique and After&hellip;</em>, 123&ndash;37.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote19anc\" name=\"sdfootnote19sym\">19</a>Chin-Tao Wu, <em>Privatising Culture</em> (London: Verso, 2003).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote20anc\" name=\"sdfootnote20sym\">20</a>Mel Evans, <em>Artwash: Big Oil and the Arts</em> (London: PlutoPress, 2015).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote21anc\" name=\"sdfootnote21sym\">21</a>Edit Andr&aacute;s, &ldquo;Vigorous Flagging in the Heart of Europe: The Hungarian Homeland under the Right-Wing Regime,&rdquo; <em>e-flux journal</em>, September 2014, <a href=\"https://www.e-flux.com/journal/57/60438/vigorous-flagging-in-the-heart-of-europe-the-hungarian-homeland-under-the-right-wing-regime/\">https://www.e-flux.com/journal/57/60438/vigorous-flagging-in-the-heart-of-europe-the-hungarian-homeland-under-the-right-wing-regime/</a>, accessed August 23, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote22anc\" name=\"sdfootnote22sym\">22</a>Piotr Piotrowski, &ldquo;Making the National Museum Critical,&rdquo; in <em>From Museum Critique to the Critical Museum</em>, 99&ndash;115.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote23anc\" name=\"sdfootnote23sym\">23</a>Alistair Hudson, &ldquo;Middlesbrough Institute of Modern Art: Where Do We Go from Here? Vision Statement for 2015&ndash;2018&rdquo; (Middlesbrough: MIMA, 2015), 4.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote24anc\" name=\"sdfootnote24sym\">24</a>The concepts of useful art and usership are addressed in the reader <em>What is the use?</em> published by L&rsquo;internationale in 2016. <em>What&rsquo;s the Use?: Constellations of Art, History, and Knowledge: A&nbsp;Critical Reader</em>, eds. Nick Aikens, Thomas Lange, Jorinde Seijdel, and Steven ten Thije (Amsterdam: Valiz, 2016).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote25anc\" name=\"sdfootnote25sym\">25</a> <a href=\"http://museumarteutil.net/about/\">http://museumarteutil.net/about/</a>, accessed October 21, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote26anc\" name=\"sdfootnote26sym\">26</a>John Byrne, &ldquo;Negotiating Jeopardy. Towards a&nbsp;Constituent Architecture of Use,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum: Constellations of Knowledge, Politics and Mediation: A&nbsp;Generator of Social Change</em>, eds. John Byrne, Elinor Morgan, November Paynter, Aida Sanchez de Serdio, and Adela Zeleznik (Amsterdam: Valiz, 2018), 92&ndash;114.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote27anc\" name=\"sdfootnote27sym\">27</a>Elinor Morgan, &ldquo;Middlesbrough&rsquo;s New Communities,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum&hellip;</em>, 50&ndash;56.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote28anc\" name=\"sdfootnote28sym\">28</a> Alistair Hudson, &ldquo;Middlesbrough Institute of Modern Art: Where Do We Go from Here? Vision Statement for 2015&ndash;2018&rdquo;&hellip;</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote29anc\" name=\"sdfootnote29sym\">29</a>Rasheed Araeen, <em>Art beyond Art: Ecoaesthetics: A&nbsp;Manifesto for the 21st Century</em> (London: Third Text Publ, 2010).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote30anc\" name=\"sdfootnote30sym\">30</a>Rasheed Araeen, &ldquo;Food for Thought. Thought for Change,&rdquo; in <em>Art beyond Art: Ecoaesthetics: A&nbsp;Manifesto for the 21st Century</em> (London: Third Text Publications, 2010), 129&ndash;43.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote31anc\" name=\"sdfootnote31sym\">31</a>Kuba Szreder, Sebastian Cichocki, and Meagan Down, &ldquo;Constituencies-Art-Nexus: The Br&oacute;dno Sculpture Park Case,&rdquo; in <em>Deviant Practice</em>, ed. Nick Aikens (Eindhoven: Van Abbemuseum, 2018), 238&ndash;56.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote32anc\" name=\"sdfootnote32sym\">32</a>Tania Bruguera, &ldquo;Arte &Uacute;til,&rdquo; in <em>Truth Is Concrete: A&nbsp;Handbook for Artistic Strategies in Real Politics</em>, ed. Florian Malzacher (Berlin; New York; Graz: Sternberg Press; Steirischer Herbst, 2014), 299&ndash;301</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote33anc\" name=\"sdfootnote33sym\">33</a> John Byrne, &ldquo;Social Autonomy and the Use Value of Art,&rdquo; <em>Afterall</em>, no.&nbsp;42 (Autumn/Winter 2016), <a href=\"https://www.afterall.org/journal/issue.42/social-autonomy-and-the-use-value-of-art\">https://www.afterall.org/journal/issue.42/social-autonomy-and-the-use-value-of-art</a>, accessed August 23, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote34anc\" name=\"sdfootnote34sym\">34</a>Michael Hardt and Antonio Negri, <em>Commonwealth</em> (Cambridge (Mass.): Harvard University Press, 2009); Massimo De Angelis, &ldquo;Reflections on Alternatives, Commons and Communities or Building a&nbsp;New World from the Bottom Up,&rdquo; <em>The Commoner</em>, 2003; An Architektur, Massimo De Angelis, and Stavros Stavrides, &ldquo;On the Commons: A&nbsp;Public Interview with Massimo De Angelis and Stavros Stavrides,&rdquo; <em>e-Flux Journal</em>, 2010, <a href=\"http://www.e-flux.com/journal/on-the-commons-a-public-interview-with-massimo-de-angelis-and-stavros-stavrides/\">http://www.e-flux.com/journal/on-the-commons-a-public-interview-with-massimo-de-angelis-and-stavros-stavrides/</a>, accessed October 21, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote35anc\" name=\"sdfootnote35sym\">35</a>John Byrne, &ldquo;Architectures of Use: Introduction,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum&hellip;</em>, 76.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote36anc\" name=\"sdfootnote36sym\">36</a>After: Janna Graham, &ldquo;Negotiating Institutions,&rdquo; in Ibid., 45.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote37anc\" name=\"sdfootnote37sym\">37</a>Claire Bishop, Dan Perjovschi, <em>Radical Museology</em>&hellip;</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote38anc\" name=\"sdfootnote38sym\">38</a>Manuel, Borja-Villel, &ldquo;<em>Really Useful Knowledge</em>,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum</em>&hellip;</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote39anc\" name=\"sdfootnote39sym\">39</a><em>From Museum Critique to the Critical Museum</em>&hellip;</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote40anc\" name=\"sdfootnote40sym\">40</a>Vasif Kortun, &ldquo;Questions on Institutions,&rdquo; <em>SALT.TXT</em> (blog), January 12, 2018, <a href=\"http://blog.saltonline.org/post/169608730654/questions-on-institutions\">http://blog.saltonline.org/post/169608730654/questions-on-institutions</a>, accessed August 23, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote41anc\" name=\"sdfootnote41sym\">41</a>Vasif Kortun, &ldquo;IN TURKISH THE WORD &lsquo;PUBLIC&rsquo; DOESN&rsquo;T EXIST: Vasif Kortun in Conversation with the Editors,&rdquo; in <em>I Can&rsquo;t Work like This: A&nbsp;Reader on Recent Boycotts and Contemporary Art</em>, ed. Joanna Warsza (Berlin: Sternberg Press, 2017), 133&ndash;40.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote42anc\" name=\"sdfootnote42sym\">42</a>Jes&uacute;s Carrillo, &ldquo;Conspiratorial Institutions? Museums and Social Transformation in the Post-Crisis Period,&rdquo; <em>Wrong Wrong Magazine</em>, June 26, 2017, <a href=\"http://wrongwrong.net/article/conspiratorial-institutions-museums-and-social-transformation-in-the-post-crisis-period\">http://wrongwrong.net/article/conspiratorial-institutions-museums-and-social-transformation-in-the-post-crisis-period</a>, accessed August 24, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote43anc\" name=\"sdfootnote43sym\">43</a>Charles Esche, &ldquo;The Deviant Art Institution,&rdquo; in <em>Performing the Institution(Al), Volume 1</em>, ed. Kunsthalle Lissabon (Lisboa: Kunsthalle Lissabon; ATLAS Projectos, 2010).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote44anc\" name=\"sdfootnote44sym\">44</a>Simon Sheikh, ed., <em>In the Place of the Public Sphere?</em> (Berlin: b_books, 2005); Michael Warner, <em>Publics and Counterpublics</em> (New York: Zone Books, 2005); Rosalyn Deutsche, <em>Evictions: Art and Spatial Politics</em> (Chicago, Ill: Graham Foundation for Advanced Studies in the Fine Arts, 1996); Oskar Negt and Alexander Kluge, <em>Public Sphere and Experience: Toward an Analysis of the Bourgeois and Proletarian Public Sphere</em> (Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press, 1993); Ewa Majewska, <em>Kontrpubliczności Ludowe i&nbsp;Feministyczne. Wczesna &ldquo;Solidarność&rdquo; i&nbsp;Czarne Protesty</em> (Warszawa: Książka i&nbsp;Prasa, 2018).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote45anc\" name=\"sdfootnote45sym\">45</a>Maria Lind, &ldquo;Tensta Museum L&rsquo;Internationale,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum: Constellations of Knowledge, Politics and Mediation : A&nbsp;Generator of Social Change</em>, ed. John Byrne et al. (Amsterdam: Valiz, 2018), 76&ndash;80.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote46anc\" name=\"sdfootnote46sym\">46</a>Janna Graham, &ldquo;Negotiating Institutions,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum: Constellations of Knowledge, Politics and Mediation : A&nbsp;Generator of Social Change</em>, ed. John Byrne et al. (Amsterdam: Valiz, 2018), 76&ndash;80.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote47anc\" name=\"sdfootnote47sym\">47</a>Kuba Szreder, Ewa Majewska, &ldquo;So Far, So Good: Contemporary Fascism, Weak Resistance, and Postartistic Practices in Today&rsquo;s Poland,&rdquo; <em>e-flux journal</em>, no. 47 (October 2016), <a href=\"http://www.e-flux.com/journal/76/71467/so-far-so-good-contemporary-fascism-weak-resistance-and-postartistic-practices-in-today-s-poland/\">http://www.e-flux.com/journal/76/71467/so-far-so-good-contemporary-fascism-weak-resistance-and-postartistic-practices-in-today-s-poland/</a>, accessed August 24, 2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote48anc\" name=\"sdfootnote48sym\">48</a>Michael Hardt, Antonio Negri, <em>Commonwealth</em> (Cambridge, Mass.: Harvard University Press, 2009).</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote49anc\" name=\"sdfootnote49sym\">49</a>Claire Bishop, Dan Perjovschi, <em>Radical Museology</em>&hellip;</p>\n<p><a href=\"#sdfootnote50anc\" name=\"sdfootnote50sym\">50</a>RedCSur, &ldquo;Archives in Use. A&nbsp;Laboratory of Political Imagination for the Present,&rdquo; in <em>The Constituent Museum&hellip;</em>, 316&ndash;22.</p>');
